### LXXII

### TO CHERISH ONE'S SELF

When people are too ignorant to fear the fearsome thing, then it will
surely come. Do not make the place where they dwell confining, the life
they live wearisome. If they are let alone, they will not become
restless. Therefore the wise man while not understanding himself regards
himself, while cherishing he does not overvalue himself. Therefore he
discards flattery and prefers regard.

